sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K510041
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This plasmid can be used for visualization purposes or to brand a strain because of its insertion in the genome of the working organism and split the antibiotic resistance cassette with the temporary expression of Flp recombinase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: David Caballero, Fernando Govantes
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The miniTn7BB-Gm minitransposon was synthesized commercially and pUC18SfiI is a commercial vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The BBa_I13521 BioBrick was inserted within the BCS of pUC18Sfi-miniTn7BB-Gm by EcoRI and PstI clonning. In order to construct the pUC18Sfi-miniTn7BB-Gm delivery plasmid, the miniTn7BB-Gm transposon was cleaved from the commercial plasmid pMA (Mr. Gene) with SfiI and ligated to SfiI-digested pUC18Sfi. This strategy removes all multi-cloning restriction sites from pUC18Sfi, except for the flanking SfiI, thus guaranteeing that the unique sites in the transposon are not duplicated. The remove of the multi-cloning restriction sites was verify by analytic digestions.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K510000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The miniTn7BB-Gm synthetic minitransposon was digested at the flanking SfiI sites and cloned into SfiI-digested pUC18-Sfi. This results in the elimination of the complete pUC18-SfiI multi-cloning site, except for the duplicated SfiI sites that remain on both sides of the transposon, thus facilitating its transfer to other vectors. This plasmid can be used to keep the mini-Tn7-Gm in E. coli and other enterics, and may be used for transposition into the genomes of non-enteric bacteria, in which it is non-replicative. The structure of the mini-Tn7BB-Gm transposon is shown in the figure below. Tn7R and Tn7L are the right and left ends of Tn7 transposon, respectively, required for recognition of the transposase machinery and transposition. FRT is the Flp recombinase target site for excision of the resistance once the transposon is inserted in the genome of a living organism. The gentamycin resistance cassette (Gm) is flanked by restriction sites in order to facilitate the generation of variants with different antibiotic resistance markers. The BioBrick cloning site (BCS) includes the prefix and suffix restrictions sites used in assembly standard 10, and it is the place where BioBricks are inserted for genome integration. The complete construction is flanked by SfiI restriction sites to facilitate cloning.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: David Caballero, Fernando Govantes
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
The pUC18-SfiI cloning vector was kindly provided by the Microbiology laboratory of Centro Andaluz de Biolog??a del Desarrollo (CABD) in Sevilla. The miniTn7BB-Gm synthetic transposon was designed by the iGEM 2011 team UPO-Sevilla based on the set of miniTn7 derivatives developed by Choi et al. (2005) and commercially synthesized by Mr. Gene (Regensburg, Germany).
K.-H. Choi, J. B. Gaynor, K. G. White, C. Lopez, C. M. Bosio, R. R. Karkhoff-Schweizer & H. P. Schweizer (2005). A Tn7-based broad-range bacterial cloning and expression system. Nature Methods, vol.2 NO.6, June 2005, 443.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In order to make this vector compatible with assembly standard 10, several restriction sites were removed from the synthetic sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
